    <abstract>
      <t>Directed ARP is a dynamic address resolution procedure that enables hosts and routers to resolve advertised potential next-hop IP addresses on foreign IP networks to their associated link level addresses.  This memo defines an Experimental Protocol for the Internet community.
	 </t>
    </abstract>
